article.headline: N.C. Central 67, Coppin St. 65
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Bryan Ayala and Philip Branch each scored 21 points, and North Carolina Central defeated Coppin State 67-65 on Wednesday night. Ayala landed three of four free throws in the final minute of the game to help N.C. Central win. Tremain Holloway put N.C. Central ahead, 64-62, with a layup with 35 seconds to play. Ayala made two free throws with 22 seconds left, extending the lead to 66-62. He then made one of two free throws with six seconds remaining, giving N.C. Central a five-point lead. Coppin's Tywain McKee sank a three-point basket at the buzzer, bringing the final score to 67-65. Charles Futrell grabbed a game-high eight rebounds for N.C. Central (2-23). McKee lead Coppin State (4-18) with a team-high 19 points.
